		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Go earn whatever items you want.&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't think for a second that those twinked people that you see didn't earn it, in time.  Once you get a character up past 50, you'll have spent a great deal of time in the game.  With that much time and effort invested, it's more like a reward to be able to twink a new character.  I was in the same boat as you when I first started out.  I made a vow never to twink, because it would take away from the meaning of the game.  Well, I discovered that meaning of the game was not in acquiring material (or immaterial...whatever) goods.  It's in grouping with others and making friends all over the world.  Trust me, once you get up there, you'll see what I'm talking about.<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>40th circle pally of virtue</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
