		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=600"><span id=Guru>PraetorFenix</span></a><b><span id=Guru><br>Guru</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>279 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.92]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Like Souldragoon, I also used to be very anti-twinking.&nbsp;&nbsp;I felt that people with items beyond their level were all filthy eBay-ers, and should be hung.<br><br>Looking back however, it was really just jealousy.  I really wanted a Ghoulbane, a SoulFire, and a Fiery Avenger.  I wanted to have full Valorium and Ro in the bank while I carted around a bunch of Deepwater for my normal battles.<br><br>Now, I'm typing this up a few minutes before I'm about to go up to the Plane of Fear to get that Valorium I've been dreaming about.  I have three pieces of Deepwater already, and have most of the quest components for the new Fiery Defender (upgrade to the Fiery Avenger).<br><br>Melee gear isn't as hard to get as it's made out to be.  Did you know that some caster spells are only gotten through the Spell Research trade skill?  A necromancer's Summon Corpse spell can cost them up to 1000 platnium off of a once every 48 hours spawn deep in Splitpaw.  And level 50+ spells, I won't really go there, other than to say that some of them cost more than half my armour.<br><br>Some of the best items are the cheapest ones.  Jagged Bands are 5 AC and 3 strength, and will cost maybe 50 platnium for a pair.  Shin Greaves and Gauntlets are free.  Bronze, while heavy, some people will just <i>give</i> away to newer players.  As a paladin you have access to the free Marr's Promise shield in the Rathe Mountains.  14 AC is nothng to sneeze at, especially for zero cost.<br><br>The damage caps Verant set in are only in effect for the lower levels (less than 20).  After that your damage will slowly increase every level.  this is an excellent way to prevent heavy twinking.  Could you imagine a level 1 twink with a Throneblade of the Ykesha, hitting for 130 damage a pop?  They're there for a VERY good reason I'd say.  This also allows people to get gifts from friends they make.  And isn't community the primary goal of EverQuest?<br><br>In time, you too shall become great Anonymous original poster.  It just takes effort, a willingness to make good friends, and a little luck.  I am currently unguilded as well.  You don't need to be in a big and evil "UBER GUILD" to get ahead (not to say uber guilds are evil.  I have friends who are members of them, and they're great guys).<br><br>Your day will come soon.  It just takes some patience.  That is one of a paladin's virtues, isn't it? :)</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><b>Praetor</b>, 65th Lord Protector of Ascent (Retired)<br><b>Tiresias</b>, 1st Warrior of Asura (Hopefully)</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=97311650223974&num=3&page=&post=1&mid=97311650223974><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>3 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
